NOTES:
------
Â· [ ]  -  refers to optional parts of a command.

Â· '[n]' or '[m]'  -  always decimal numbers, containing one or more ASCII
  digits to express their value.

Â· Where '[n]' occurs in a command and the value of 'n' is not explicitly
  defined, it usually defaults to 1.

Â· 'ESC'  -  an ESCape key press (HEX $1B or DECIMAL 27) - Use CTRL-[ if you
  don't have an ESCape key (Commodore 64's, for instance) - in some
  implementations, $DB also works as a command introducer, but ESC is much
  more widely-used

Â· Commands involving upper or lower-case letters are always case-sensitive.

Â· Where applicable, the equivalent C-Net MCI commands (version 2.0 and
  beyond) have been included for reference.

Â· All sequences should be entered WITHOUT SPACES - the spaces are included
  for readability only.


