CHANGING COLOURS
================

NOTES:
------
Â· If Reverse Display is activated, the foreground colour becomes the
  background colour

Â· In SkyPix mode, the first 8 colours can be accessed with standard ANSI
  commands (to allow compatibility with ANSI screens), however the second
  8 SkyPix colours can only be accessed by changing the SkyPix [7mPen Colour[0m,
  which is discussed later in this text.

Â· Only the first 8 colours may be used as a background.

Â· The foreground and background colours can be mixed and matched to achieve
  128 total colour combinations.


