SkyPix is defined as a sub-set of the ANSI standard, and in fact most ANSI
commands have the same effect in SkyPix mode.  There are however several
SkyPix-specific commands (each followed with a characteristic "!" [bang]
terminator) which can only be used from a terminal equipped to emulate the
SkyPix protocol (all 2 of 'em ;)

NOTES:
------
Â· All SkyPix graphics are implemented on a default screen of 640x200
  (8 colours) with the [7mdefault palette[0m described below (unless the palette
  or number of number of [7mbitplanes[0m is changed.)

Â· All sequences should be entered WITHOUT SPACES - the spaces are included
  for readability only.

Commands:
[7m 1 - SET PIXEL          [0m [7m 9 - PLAY SAMPLE        [0m [7m16 - XMODEM TRANSFER    [0m
[7m 2 - DRAW LINE          [0m [7m10 - SET FONT           [0m [7m17 - SET DISPLAY MODE   [0m
[7m 3 - AREA FILL          [0m [7m11 - NEW PALETTE        [0m [7m18 - SET PEN B COLOUR   [0m
[7m 4 - RECTANGLE FILL     [0m [7m12 - RESET PALETTE      [0m [7m19 - POSITION CURSOR    [0m
[7m 5 - ELLIPSE            [0m [7m13 - FILLED ELLIPSE     [0m 20 - (NOT IMPLEMENTED)
[7m 6 - GRAB BRUSH         [0m [7m14 - DELAY (PAUSE)      [0m [7m21 - CONTROLLER RETURN  [0m
[7m 7 - USE BRUSH (BLIT)   [0m [7m15 - SET PEN A COLOUR   [0m [7m22 - DEFINE GADGET      [0m
